/// `tls_accept` in `std.tls`.
///
/// ## Example
/// ```aic
/// // Import `std.tls` and call `tls_accept` with module-specific arguments.
/// ```
///
/// ## Effects
/// See the function signature for required effects and capabilities.
///
/// ## Errors
/// Returns module-defined error variants when the operation fails.
fn tls_accept(listener_handle: Int, config: TlsConfig) -> Result[TlsStream, TlsError] effects { net } {
    tls_accept_timeout(listener_handle, config, 30000)
}

